451 is excited to share a digital bundle of our sold out first issues from 2015! Inside you will find stories of horror, mayhem, werewolves, storage containers, love, zombies and cults. This bundle Includes the Williams Brother's EXMORTIS, Scott Rosenberg's BAD MOON RISING, Clay McLeod Chapman's SELF STORAGE, Mark Mallouk's SUNFLOWER, George Pelecanos' SIX and A.J. Gentile's HUMBUG!

Celebrate the 75th anniversary of Archie Comics with this special retrospective presentation! Starting out as a seasonal magazine, Archie Giant Series evolved into a wide branding for one-shot specials -- a little bit like Pep Digital. Archie Giant Series is a bit of a mysterious entry in the Archie Library -- the numbering goes up to #632, but there are only 332 issues! In this collection, we'll look through the series history and show you some of the highlights.
name: Archie Giant Series

description: Each issue of Marvel Previews is a comic book-sized, 120-page, full-color guide and preview to all of Marvel's upcoming releases - it's your #1 source for advanced information on Marvel Comics! This February issue features items scheduled to ship in April 2016 and beyond.

After being shot with the red angel arrow of love by Saki, the girl he has a crush on, Mirai spends the next 33 days happily at her beck and call. Once he returns to his sense, the two of them enter into an alliance in order to protect themselves from the other god candidates. Meanwhile, the god candidate posing as the superhero Metropoliman summons the others to a baseball stadium. Knowing it's a trap, Mirai goes anyway...
name: Chapter 5: The Big Reveal

description:
In September 1969, after the embarrassing failure of Apollo 11, the USSR is the first to have a manned landing on the moon - winning the highly symbolic space race with the USA. In the wake of this achievement, President Nixon furiously demands that NASA send up and install a permanent base on the moon...

Ten years later, the Cold War enters a critical phase and the face-off between the opposing Americans and Russians may now take place on the moon!
name: Russians On the Moon!

description:
What would have happened if the Dallas attack had taken place in 1973?

Washington D.C., 1965. The re-elected President has decided to begin his second term with a decisive ground offensive into Communist North Vietnam. At the same time, protest actions in the USA are increasing, against the war and the dictatorial military junta.

'French', who volunteered to serve in Vietnam, is participating in the bloodiest, most dangerous missions until he is suddenly declared missing. On November 22, 1973, he turns up in Dallas in the rest room of a bar, where he picks up a sniper rifle...
name: Who Killed the President?

description: Can the heroes of newly formed Red Lance stop the controlled mind of Cataclysm as he ravages the city?
What plot does Rupinella Daniels have in mind for Red Lance? What will Vycia and Cataclysm do next? What chaos has spawned on the streets of Centerpoint?

Larger-than-life MMA fighter Rampage Jackson faces his toughest opponents yet in this super-powered slug-fest; and this time the stakes are much higher than a championship belt! Rampage Jackson has touched the lives of millions, and when one of them reaches out for help against a terrible threat, he swings into action. Rampage is different this time; with astonishing new super powers and his faithful dog, Andronicus, by his side, he must prepare for bone-crunching throwdowns in over-the-top adventures that take him around the world, to other worlds, and through time itself! An anthology of amazing self-contained stories, Rampage Jackson: Street Soldier marks the beginning of a bold new era of superhero fun! Collecting Rampage Jackson: Street Soldier #1-5
name: Vol. 1

description: Mixed martial arts super star Rampage Jackson explodes into his own regular series from Lion Forge Comics! Rampage Jackson is called upon by an old friend to help her out after she's stumble upon the story of a lifetime. What she doesn't know is that Rampage and his faithful dog Andronicus have changed. They now have super powers and are more than willing to use them to defeat the bad guys. When bad things happen to good people Rampage doesn't have a problem getting ugly to make things right! Collects Rampage Jackson Street Soldier issues #6-14!
name: Vol. 2
